On Sat, Feb 06, 1999 at 12:09:11AM +0100, Peter Schlaile wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> The DOS-NCSA FTP-Client can't do downloads from a 2.2.0-Linux-Box anymore.
> They start slowly and then stop suddenly. 
> 2.0.x worked fine. (Path MTU discovery is not the problem, I tried this
> already ;-) 
> The problem is reproducible on two different Linux boxes and clients. 
> 
> What should I do? 
Try hardcoding the "arp" entry for the client (Same LAN segment isnt it ?)
via the "arp" command
I had a bug which showed up downloading a kernel via tftp
from a client which did not respond to arp requests during download
this might also apply to the DOS NCSA FTP Client.
